s:1267:"<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><strong>Course Completion Requirements: Creative Writing</strong></span><br /></p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">To complete the Creative Writing course, you need to:</p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><br /></span></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ol><li><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><strong>Complete All Modules:</strong> Successfully finish each module, covering key topics such as narrative structure, character development, dialogue, and writing styles.</span></li><li><strong>Pass Quizzes and Assessments:</strong> Achieve a passing score on all quizzes and assessments to demonstrate your understanding of creative writing techniques and concepts.</li><li><strong>Participate in Writing Exercises:</strong> Engage in all writing exercises to practice and refine your creative skills.</li><li><strong>Achieve a Minimum Grade: </strong>Attain the minimum grade set to ensure a solid grasp of creative writing fundamentals.</li></ol><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">Upon meeting these requirements, you will have demonstrated a strong ability to create compelling narratives and effectively use creative writing techniques, setting the stage for further development in your writing journey.</p>";